  "original_title": "\u2018\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb8\u0bcd\u2019 \u0b9a\u0ba9\u0bbf \u0bb5\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b9e\u0bbe\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bcb\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sunday delivery if 'gas' arrives on Saturday",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe told the House that the shortage of cooking gas in the country will end by the end of this month or the beginning of August and said that the government is confident that gas can be supplied without shortage for the remaining four months.",
        "Ranil said the above while responding to an oral question raised in the Parliament regarding the issue of cooking gas.",
        "He said that if the amount of gas is received on the 9th as planned, it will be possible to distribute the gas throughout the country on the 11th.",
        "He also informed that on 11th and 12th, gas can be distributed throughout the city of Colombo. Actions have been taken to distribute one lakh 40 thousand cylinders of 12.5 kg gas at 140 stations in Colombo. He said that it is planned to distribute one lakh 11 thousand cylinders across the country on a daily basis."
      ],
